'''Canada's World''' is a collaborative discussion between Canadian citizens, universities and organizations on Canada's role in the world started in 2007.  Topics include economic development, diversity, and promotion of human rights.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.themarknews.com/videos/453|title=Canada's World calls on citizens to make Canada a global leader|date=24 February 2010|work=The Mark|accessdate=25 February 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091219223121/http://themarknews.com/videos/453#|archive-date=2009-12-19|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>  Participating citizens have expressed a sense of disconnect with the government.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/comment/columnists/article/600724|title=How to be a role model for the world|date=Mar 12, 2009|work=[[Toronto Star]]|accessdate=25 February 2010 | first=Bob | last=Hepburn}}</ref>

