'''''Echinscus clavispinosus''''' is a [[species]] of [[tardigrade]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Echiniscidae]].<ref name="Degma, Bertolani & Guidetti">{{Cite work|last=Degma|first=Peter|last2=Bertolani|first2=Roberto |last3=Guidetti |first3=Roberto|date=30 June 2018|title=Actual checklist of Tardigrada species (2009-2018) |url=http://www.tardigrada.modena.unimo.it/miscellanea/Actual%20checklist%20of%20Tardigrada.pdf |publisher=[[University of Modena and Reggio Emilia]] |version=34th Ed.|access-date=25 November 2018 }}</ref> The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands and is found only in the [[Santo Antão, Cape Verde|island of Santo Antão]].<ref name="Fontoura, Pilato & Lisi">{{cite journal|authors=Fontoura, Pilato & Lisi|journal=[[Zootaxa]]|title=Tardigrada from Santo Antão Island (Archipelago of Cape Verde, West Africa) with the description of a new species|url=http://mapress.com/zootaxa/2011/f/z02838p040f.pdf|volume= 2838|year=2011 |pages= 30-40}}</ref> The species was first described by [[Paulo Fontoura]], [[Giovanni Pilato]] and [[Oscar Lisi]] in 2011.<ref name="Fontoura, Pilato & Lisi"/>

