{{Italic title}} '''''Fedraheimen''''' was a [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] weekly magazine, issued from 1877 to 1891.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fedraheimen|url=https://snl.no/Fedraheimen|work=Store norske leksikon|accessdate=23 May 2015|language=Norwegian|date=14 February 2009}}</ref>
==History and profile== [[File:Fedraheimen.jpg|thumb|Fedraheimen]] [[Arne Garborg]] founded ''Fedraheimen'' in 1877<ref>{{cite web|title=2011-12-programs|url=http://www.rawsonduo.com/2011-12-programs/Nordlys/Nordlys%202011%20Program.pdf|publisher=Rawson Duo|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> and edited it until 1882. [[Ivar Mortensson-Egnund]] was editor until 1889, and [[Rasmus Steinsvik]] until it ceased publication in 1891. The magazine was a proponent for the [[Nynorsk]] language. Among the contributors to the magazine were [[Ivar Aasen]], [[Anders Hovden]], [[Kristofer Janson]], [[Nils Kjær]], [[Hans Seland]] and [[Vetle Vislie]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Fedraheimen |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Fedraheimen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=10 May 2010}}</ref>
Parts of the magazine have been made available on-line.
