[[File:Teatr STU.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Theater Scena STU]]
'''Theater Scena STU''' ('''Krakowski Teatr Scena STU''') is located at 16 Krasinskiego Street in [[Kraków]], [[Poland]].  Established in 1966 by [[Krzysztof Jasiński]],<ref name="Filler1977">{{cite book|last=Filler|first=Witold|title=Contemporary Polish theatre|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8HJgAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=19 September 2011|year=1977|publisher=Interpress|page=69}}</ref> it started as a member of a group of nonprofessional student theaters.<ref name="Kubik1994">{{cite book|last=Kubik|first=Jan|title=The power of symbols against the symbols of power: the rise of Solidarity and the fall of state socialism in Poland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5VzX_0glK7EC&pg=PA78|accessdate=18 September 2011|year=1994|publisher=Penn State Press|isbn=978-0-271-01084-7|pages=78–}}</ref> It is considered to be one of the city's most important cultural institutions.<ref name="TerterovReuvid2005">{{cite book|last1=Terterov|first1=Marat|last2=Reuvid|first2=Jonathan|title=Doing Business with Poland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Dk2vlUQESaIC&pg=PA326|accessdate=18 September 2011|date=1 September 2005|publisher=GMB Publishing Ltd|isbn=978-1-905050-64-2|pages=326–}}</ref>  The current artistic director is Krzysztof Jasiński.<ref>http://www.scenastu.com.pl/?show=dzieje&itemID=1&do=doChangeLanguage&langID=en</ref>

